why is this assuming that a content can't ber in simultaneous subscriptions?
Can't a reproducible content be sent to two different requests at the same time?
I don't think the abstract content should hold onto a subscription reference at all. it just needs logic like:
    boolean oneTimeused;
    ...
    if (!isReproducible|())
    {
      if (oneTimeUsed)
          throw ISE(...);
      oneTimeUsed = true;
    }
    ...

